  "text": "Found 7 deprecated classes in the Apache Flink DataStream API under flink-streaming-java/src/main/. The deprecated classes include:\n\n1. **TextInputFormat** (flink-streaming-java/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/legacy/io/TextInputFormat.java) - An input format for reading text files. Marked with @Deprecated annotation. Replacement: Use FLIP-27 FileSource and Sink-V2 FlinkSink for reading/writing text files.\n\n2. **TextOutputFormat** (flink-streaming-java/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/legacy/io/TextOutputFormat.java) - An output format for writing objects to text files. Marked with @Deprecated annotation. Replacement: Use FLIP-27 FileSource and Sink-V2 FlinkSink for reading/writing text files.\n\n3. **AscendingTimestampExtractor** (flink-streaming-java/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/functions/timestamps/AscendingTimestampExtractor.java) - A timestamp assigner and watermark generator for monotonously ascending timestamps. Marked with @Deprecated annotation. Replacement: Not specified in the deprecation javadoc.\n\n4. **DiscardingSink** (flink-streaming-java/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/functions/sink/legacy/DiscardingSink.java) - A stream sink that ignores all elements. Marked as deprecated in javadoc. Replacement: Use org.apache.flink.streaming.api.functions.sink.v2.DiscardingSink.\n\n5. **DataGeneratorSource** (flink-streaming-java/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/functions/source/datagen/DataGeneratorSource.java) - A data generator source for testing and startup. Marked as deprecated in javadoc. Replacement: Use org.apache.flink.connector.datagen.source.DataGeneratorSource.\n\n6. **TwoPhaseCommitSinkFunction** (flink-streaming-java/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/functions/sink/legacy/TwoPhaseCommitSinkFunction.java) - A base class for exactly-once semantic sink functions using two-phase commit. Marked as deprecated in javadoc. Replacement: Use org.apache.flink.api.connector.sink2.Sink.\n\n7. **StreamingFileSink** (flink-streaming-java/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/functions/sink/filesystem/legacy/StreamingFileSink.java) - A sink that emits elements to FileSystem files within buckets. Marked as deprecated in javadoc. Replacement: Use org.apache.flink.connector.file.sink.FileSink.\n\nThese deprecated classes are primarily I/O format classes (TextInputFormat, TextOutputFormat), sink functions (DiscardingSink, TwoPhaseCommitSinkFunction, StreamingFileSink), a source function (DataGeneratorSource), and a timestamp extractor (AscendingTimestampExtractor). All are located in the flink-streaming-java/src/main directory and are being replaced by newer implementations in the Flink connector ecosystem and FLIP-27 improvements."
}

